choices.text: You are given an array of integers. You are asked to find the minimum value of a function of two integers. The function is defined as (i - j)^2 + g(i, j)^2. The function g is calculated by the following pseudo-code: int g(int i, int j) {     int sum = 0;     for (int k = min(i, j) + 1; k <= max(i, j); k = k + 1)        sum = sum + a[k];     return sum; }
